= Details of your current circumstances

My name is Leonardo de Andrade Santos. I hold a Bachelor's degree in Electrical Engineering from the University Federal of Paraná (_Universidade Federal do Paraná_ - UFPR), Brazil, and I am currently finalising my Master's thesis in Electrical Engineering at the same institution, with research focused on digital signal processing and VHDL implementation. I am temporarily residing in Gold Coast, Queensland, as my wife, Anielle Mendes de Oliveira an architect completes an English language program here. I have approximately four years of professional experience in the technology sector in Brazil, working on intelligent solutions for precision agriculture. I intend to use my time in Australia productively by undertaking a coursework-based qualification that complements my existing engineering background.

= Reason for choosing to study this course in Australia with Kaplan

My academic career in Brazil has been strongly research-oriented, providing me with a solid theoretical foundation in engineering and signal processing. However, I recognise that to advance professionally in the IT field both in Brazil and internationally I need formal, practice-based qualifications in applied computing. The Master of Information Technology at Kaplan Business School offers exactly this: a structured, industry-focused curriculum covering software engineering, systems integration, and emerging technologies, directly complementing my engineering expertise.

I chose the Gold Coast campus at Kaplan because it allows me to study during the period my wife is already based in Australia, making this a practical and efficient use of my time abroad. I am fully aware of the program's attendance requirements, academic expectations, and associated living costs, all of which I am prepared to meet.

= Details of anticipated benefits you will gain after completing this course

Upon completing the MIT program, I expect to gain several concrete professional benefits. First, the qualification will formalise and broaden my IT competencies — particularly in software engineering and systems integration — skills that are directly applicable to the technology and agribusiness sectors in Brazil, where demand for professionals with interdisciplinary engineering and IT backgrounds is growing significantly. Second, the practical curriculum will allow me to develop skills that complement my research background, making me a more competitive professional upon my return. Third, having studied at an Australian institution will provide me with an internationally recognised qualification and exposure to global industry practices, which I intend to apply within the Brazilian technology market, where such experience is highly valued by employers.

= Details of any other relevant information you would like to include

I wish to emphasise that my primary motivation for undertaking this course is professional development aligned with my career in Brazil. My academic and professional networks, family, and long-term career prospects remain centred in Brazil, where the convergence of engineering and IT is an area of growing demand — particularly in precision agriculture, embedded systems, and industrial automation. I am pursuing this qualification to strengthen the skills I will bring back to the Brazilian technology sector. My study in Australia is temporary and purposeful, and I look forward to applying what I learn upon returning home.
